18,0.0412,0.031928],"unified_progress":[0.1148,0.14881,0.11539,0.10954,0.085087,0.090251,0.06964,0.079112,0.059777,0.051344,0.04302,0.033228]},{"section":6,"text":"Hmm, the key points here are the type of pain, its duration, triggers, and location.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.072799,0.11576,0.12464,0.11849,0.10079,0.083614,0.077316,0.071797,0.061279,0.070571,0.052463,0.050478],"unified_progress":[0.082023,0.087411,0.089951,0.10184,0.098643,0.09221,0.091651,0.085099,0.075725,0.085284,0.062238,0.047921]},{"section":7,"text":"The sudden, brief, severe pain that's stabbing makes me think of neuralgia.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.069041,0.11287,0.11551,0.1104,0.099324,0.087555,0.080524,0.075702,0.067152,0.069562,0.057193,0.055162],"unified_progress":[0.072078,0.084819,0.08997,0.096367,0.095319,0.093477,0.091387,0.089397,0.082001,0.082205,0.067891,0.055087]},{"section":8,"text":"Trigeminal neuralgia is a common condition that fits this description.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047272,0.087735,0.10329,0.10956,0.10653,0.09701,0.092144,0.083106,0.074073,0.07714,0.061354,0.060792],"unified_progress":[0.045999,0.066425,0.086127,0.095057,0.097911,0.103,0.098817,0.094818,0.089321,0.088466,0.072725,0.061335]},{"section":9,"text":"The trigeminal nerve is responsible for facial sensation, so if it's affected, the pain would be in the face.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048113,0.086508,0.092796,0.097859,0.099375,0.097972,0.095772,0.090028,0.083411,0.07938,0.068032,0.060754],"unified_progress":[0.068689,0.071492,0.082387,0.091525,0.094983,0.097579,0.095095,0.094384,0.089372,0.083775,0.071107,0.059612]},{"section":10,"text":"Trigeminal neuralgia typically presents with paroxysmal (sudden, recurrent) electric shock-like or stabbing pain in one side of the face.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049422,0.085975,0.087823,0.093111,0.097742,0.099124,0.09764,0.09275,0.082698,0.082255,0.067971,0.063489],"unified_progress":[0.055065,0.070196,0.086429,0.09062,0.094356,0.10462,0.098218,0.096881,0.090052,0.084222,0.070575,0.05877]},{"section":11,"text":"The duration being seconds to a couple of minutes aligns with that.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057079,0.099904,0.096435,0.092034,0.090916,0.091838,0.089068,0.089152,0.080985,0.079641,0.069681,0.063266],"unified_progress":[0.063263,0.08631,0.087559,0.089927,0.091633,0.094147,0.090976,0.093279,0.08714,0.084745,0.072381,0.05864]},{"section":12,"text":"The triggers like talking (which involves moving the mouth) and exposure to cold wind are classic for this condition.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052439,0.095492,0.094841,0.092527,0.092482,0.0952,0.091857,0.090645,0.08358,0.079819,0.070377,0.060741],"unified_progress":[0.058756,0.08136,0.0861,0.089229,0.091727,0.095997,0.092895,0.094187,0.090181,0.086098,0.074692,0.058778]},{"section":13,"text":"The patient's age is also within the typical range, as it's more common in middle to older adults.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046426,0.083528,0.089584,0.093067,0.095094,0.10025,0.093653,0.091396,0.084962,0.085357,0.072882,0.063803],"unified_progress":[0.079086,0.10079,0.092672,0.090639,0.088143,0.09062,0.08619,0.089009,0.080655,0.078015,0.067888,0.056293]},{"section":14,"text":"Other possibilities to consider might be cluster headaches, but those usually present with unilateral pain around the eye, often with autonomic symptoms like tearing or nasal congestion, and they last longer (15-180 minutes).","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030807,0.066355,0.078356,0.088205,0.095617,0.099717,0.10428,0.10165,0.095271,0.093153,0.082286,0.064306],"unified_progress":[0.037217,0.065158,0.085766,0.089196,0.097699,0.10324,0.10099,0.10113,0.096775,0.094678,0.075845,0.052304]},{"section":15,"text":"Migraines can have triggers but the pain is usually throbbing and longer-lasting.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023747,0.055764,0.069795,0.081111,0.089798,0.096495,0.1057,0.10778,0.10509,0.10311,0.094096,0.067512],"unified_progress":[0.030534,0.05624,0.072738,0.081861,0.093247,0.098411,0.102,0.10783,0.10605,0.11179,0.086391,0.052914]},{"section":16,"text":"Multiple sclerosis can cause neuralgia, but there's no mention of other neurological symptoms here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019106,0.049833,0.06564,0.077194,0.085991,0.09441,0.10552,0.11062,0.11067,0.1093,0.10122,0.070499],"unified_progress":[0.027072,0.055582,0.070142,0.078697,0.090701,0.095054,0.10149,0.10941,0.10951,0.11721,0.091914,0.053227]},{"section":17,"text":"The patient's diabetes could lead to neuropathy, but diabetic neuropathy is usually more of a burning or constant pain, not the sharp, brief episodes.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02629,0.057089,0.068387,0.07881,0.08781,0.095278,0.1033,0.10604,0.10408,0.10372,0.095119,0.074081],"unified_progress":[0.033768,0.055199,0.06978,0.079523,0.089827,0.097624,0.10132,0.10699,0.10637,0.10895,0.090685,0.059969]},{"section":18,"text":"Also, the triggers here are more specific to the trigeminal nerve.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02895,0.061528,0.073816,0.082183,0.08838,0.093183,0.098138,0.099479,0.10025,0.09936,0.093325,0.081406],"unified_progress":[0.042999,0.060307,0.071663,0.081027,0.088772,0.09365,0.097619,0.10024,0.1007,0.10194,0.090101,0.070984]},{"section":19,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is trigeminal neuralgia.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033545,0.059067,0.067305,0.07325,0.076913,0.079087,0.083861,0.086731,0.091421,0.097474,0.10278,0.14856],"unified_progress":[0.037226,0.042766,0.051724,